Krispy Kreme’s U.K. Operations Bought by Investors, Times Says

-- B y   R a c h e l   G r a h a m
-- 
2011-10-16T08:05:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-16/krispy-kreme-s-u-k-operations-bought-by-investors-times-says.html
Krispy Kreme Doughnuts Inc. (KKD) ’s U.K.
operations have been bought out by management with backing from
Alcuin Capital Partners LLP, the Sunday Times reported, without
saying where it got the information.  Alcuin Capital bought a majority stake in the business for
25 million pounds ($39.6 million), according to the newspaper.
Richard Cheshire and Rob Hunt, joint managing directors at the
U.K. unit, plan to increase the number of outlets in Britain to
80 from 46 within three years, the Sunday Times said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rachel Graham in London 
